post_text:
Here is an update on the 2020-21 schedule:
-The scheduling team continues to work on the master schedule.
There was an unexpected error with Aspen this afternoon where students in Grades 10, 11, and 12 were able to view their schedules. These schedules may not have been accurate or may have been incomplete.
-We have disabled student and family accounts again and we let you know when the schedules are available.
-Grade 9 students will receive their schedules at New Student Orientation.
-In order to finish the schedule and accommodate for the necessary safety precautions we need to make this year, we will not be making any course changes.
text:
Here is an update on the 2020-21 schedule:
-The scheduling team continues to work on the master schedule.
There was an unexpected error with Aspen this afternoon where students in Grades 10, 11, and 12 were able to view their schedules. These schedules may not have been accurate or may have been incomplete.
-We have disabled student and family accounts again and we let you know when the schedules are available.
-Grade 9 students will receive their schedules at New Student Orientation.
-In order to finish the schedule and accommodate for the necessary safety precautions we need to make this year, we will not be making any course changes.

post_text: ‚ÄúYou are a light. You are the light. Never let anyone‚Äîany person or any force‚Äîdampen, dim or diminish your light. Study the path of others to make your way easier and more abundant. Lean toward the whispers of your own heart, discover the universal truth, and follow its dictates. [‚Ä¶] Release the need to hate, to harbor division, and the enticement of revenge. Release all bitterness. Hold only love, only peace in your heart, knowing that the battle of good to overcome evil is already won. Choose confrontation wisely, but when it is your time don't be afraid to stand up, speak up, and speak out against injustice. And if you follow your truth down the road to peace and the affirmation of love, if you shine like a beacon for all to see, then the poetry of all the great dreamers and philosophers is yours to manifest in a nation, a world community, and a Beloved Community that is finally at peace with itself.‚Äù -John Lewis. May you rest forever in peace. #HawkTalk #ENSATS

Now hiring School Bus Drivers for the 2020/2021 school year! Commercial Driver's License (CDL) required. Training will be provided for qualified candidates.

Work week is Monday-Friday school year calendar- 26-30 hours/week. Local routes, late runs, and charter runs available. Pay rates from $19.29 to $26.02 per hour.

Medical and Dental insurance available. Sick and Holiday pay in accordance with hours worked.

Apply online now: https://buff.ly/2Dpix6n

Take a Hike! ‚ÄúNature isn‚Äôt a miracle cure for diseases, but by interacting with it, spending time in it, experiencing it, and appreciating it, we can reap the benefits of feeling happier and healthier as a result.‚Äù

Research shows that there is a profound boost in overall health and well-being simply by leaving all technology behind and spending more time in green environments. Take advantage of how beautiful our state of Massachusetts is this summer!

Tag us in your favorite green places @hawkswellness #HawksWellnessAtHome #selfcaresunday #takeahike #HAWKTALK #ENSATS

https://buff.ly/3eTqrSN

post_text: A short story from one of our current employees who is also the parent of an alumni: ‚ÄúI work in the transportation department at Essex North Shore. I came home from work today to find my car with a flat tire! I wanted to share my daughter, Leah B., who is a North Shore Tech 2013 graduate.. who said to me, ‚ÄúI got this mom! I learned how to change a tire at the Tech my freshman year when I explored Auto.‚Äù I thought this would bring a smile to the Essex North Shore family during these tough times. Even years later, my daughter still holds the priceless knowledge she gained from her days in school. Thank you for all you do for our students- past, present and future!‚Äù #CTEMatters #CareerTechEd #HawkTalk #CreateEncouragePromoteDevelop #ENSATS

Congratulations to the Students of the Month for the month of April. Student of the Month awards are based upon teacher recommendations for students who demonstrate exemplary character and help to create a positive school environment. During this remote learning phase, our characteristics were adjusted to include: adaptability and positively trending performance in unique circumstances.

Please join us in congratulating:
Freshman - Ashley O'Brien
Sophomore - Christian Martin
Junior - Ruby Kinnon
Senior - Jordyn Barry

#ENSStudentOfTheMonth #HawkTalk #ENSATS
